scriptcs-gui
============

A simple GUI toolkit for ScriptCS

The following script shows you how to read a folder name from the <i>command argument</i> and use it with the <b>OpenFileDialog</b> helper.
<pre>
#load "../script/dialogz.csx"
// Run with:
// scriptcs -script "dialogz-demo.csx" -- c:\some-path

var folder = ScriptArgs.FirstOrDefault(); 
var path = OpenFileDialog(folder);
Console.WriteLine("You selected: '{0}'.", path ?? "nothing");
</pre>
<p>
Launch the script as shown in the picture and enjoy your interaction... :)
</p>
